  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nRight now, Solidity testing in Truffle Test uses `TestEvent`s to indicate failure.  It would probably make more sense for it to just revert, but the assertion library was written before revert messages (or reverts that didn't eat all your gas) existed.  It would almost certainly be a breaking change to change this now, but when it's time for Truffle 6, we should probably make this change.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.4.33",
